# Student lesson isolation

When working on **any** student lesson (Lesson 1, 2, 3, …), **only change that lesson**. Lessons 1 and 2 must never be affected by Lesson 3 work (or vice versa).

## Database / migrations

- Every seed or patch must be scoped to **one slug**, e.g. `WHERE slug = 'design-your-own-character'`.
- Prefer **DELETE + re-insert for that slug only** (CASCADE is fine). Never truncate or bulk-update across lessons.
- **Never** run `UPDATE student_lesson_activities` filtered only by `activity_order`, `activity_type`, or `lesson_number` without also joining `student_lessons` and filtering by **slug**.
- **Never** run SQL against the database unless the user explicitly asks.
- When suggesting manual SQL, include the slug filter in every `UPDATE`/`DELETE` and say which lesson it targets.

```sql
-- ✅ GOOD: scoped to one lesson
UPDATE student_lesson_activities la
SET content = ...
FROM student_lessons sl
WHERE sl.id = la.student_lesson_id
  AND sl.slug = 'design-your-own-character'
  AND la.activity_order = 3;

-- ❌ BAD: hits the same activity_order in ALL lessons
UPDATE student_lesson_activities
SET content = ...
WHERE activity_order = 3;
```

## Files and code

- Edit only the migration(s) for the lesson being worked on. Do not rewrite L1/L2 seed files when fixing L3.
- Shared activity components are fine; lesson-specific content lives in that lesson’s seed JSON, not copied into other lessons’ rows.

## Before handing off SQL

- Confirm the slug matches the lesson being changed.
- Confirm no statement could match rows belonging to another lesson.
